title: Add HS math pre-requisite from guidelines
body:
The [Curriculum Guidelines](https://www.amstat.org/asa/files/pdfs/EDU-DataScienceGuidelines.pdf) state the following:

> To be prepared for the data science curriculum, students should
>  * Be calculus ready (i.e., have a good precalculus course)
>  * Have an understanding of basic matrix algebra (solving systems of linear equations)
>  * Understand the basics of a relationship between variables, including scatterplots, the idea of correlation, and the line of best fit
>  * Have experience with descriptive statistics: notions of center, spread, and skew

I have found that the current curriculum, starting at MIT 6.000.1x, certainly reflects those prerequisites. Moreover, the previous Readme file included an unused "Prerequisite" link in its index, which has now been fixed.

I have also fixed a typo in the "Community" section.

title: removed unnecessary separation line in README
Added ISL course recommendation
body:
This pull request proposes the addition of the "Introduction to Statistical Learning" course to the Open Source Society University (OSSU) Data Science curriculum. This course provides a comprehensive introduction to statistical learning methods and is essential for students pursuing a career in data science.

Rationale:

Relevance to Data Science: Statistical learning is a fundamental aspect of data science, providing the necessary tools for data analysis and interpretation.

Complement Existing Curriculum: This course fills gaps in the current curriculum by offering a focused study on statistical learning techniques.

Quality of Instruction: The course is taught by renowned experts in the field and is well-received by learners for its clarity and depth. Anyone who wants to intelligently analyze complex data should own this book.” Larry Wasserman, Professor, Department of Statistics and Department of Machine Learning, CMU and author of All of Statistics

Accessibility: It's freely available online in EdX Mooc (R) or PDF download for Python or R

Practicality: The course includes hands-on exercises and real-world examples, enhancing practical understanding.

title: Update README.md

Updated Data Science curriculum README

Added new courses to the Data Science curriculum, including: 1 - CS50’s Introduction to Programming with Python (https://cs50.harvard.edu/python/2022/)

2 - CS50’s Introduction to Databases with SQL
(https://cs50.harvard.edu/sql/2024/)

3 - Learn Linear Algebra
(https://www.khanacademy.org/math/linear-algebra)

Keeping the curriculum up-to-date and enhancing user experience.

Special thanks to the OSSU community for their valuable contributions.

title: Update Math Course Links from OpenLearningLibrary to MITx Online
body: OSSU currently lists math courses on OpenLearningLibrary, but the same courses are available on MITx Online, which includes problem sets that enhance the learning experience. This issue means the current links do not fully leverage the available resources that better align with OSSU's curricular guidelines, especially in providing rigorous and comprehensive course material.
